fastPathRoutePolicy.name: fastPathRoutePolicy
fastPathRoutePolicy.description: The MIB definitions for Route Policy system.

FastpathRoutePolicyAction.name: FastpathRoutePolicyAction
FastpathRoutePolicyAction.description: Determines whether a Route Map statement should be permitted or denied.

FastpathRoutePolicyStmtIpPrecedence.name: FastpathRoutePolicyStmtIpPrecedence
FastpathRoutePolicyStmtIpPrecedence.description: Possible values of IP precedence that can be configured in a route-map statement.

fastpathRoutePolicyNameTable.name: fastpathRoutePolicyNameTable
fastpathRoutePolicyNameTable.description: Table to configure or fetch current list of route-map statements

fastpathRoutePolicyNameEntry.name: fastpathRoutePolicyNameEntry
fastpathRoutePolicyNameEntry.description: Each entry in this table corresponds to a route-map statement

fastpathRoutePolicyName.name: fastpathRoutePolicyName
fastpathRoutePolicyName.description: The name of a Route Map statement.

fastpathRoutePolicyStmtActionType.name: fastpathRoutePolicyStmtActionType
fastpathRoutePolicyStmtActionType.description: The action associated with this route-map statement. This can be either Permit/Deny

fastpathRoutePolicySequence.name: fastpathRoutePolicySequence
fastpathRoutePolicySequence.description: Route Maps are linked together using sequence numbers. All Route Maps with the same index and with different sequence numbers are linked together and processed in order of increasing sequence number.

fastpathRoutePolicyNameRowStatus.name: fastpathRoutePolicyNameRowStatus
fastpathRoutePolicyNameRowStatus.description: Controls creation and deletion of Row Status entries.

fastpathRoutePolicyStamentTable.name: fastpathRoutePolicyStamentTable
fastpathRoutePolicyStamentTable.description: Table to configure match or set statements in a route-map statement.

fastpathRoutePolicyStatementEntry.name: fastpathRoutePolicyStatementEntry
fastpathRoutePolicyStatementEntry.description: Each entry describes match and set terms in a route-map statement if configured

fastpathRoutePolicyStmtName.name: fastpathRoutePolicyStmtName
fastpathRoutePolicyStmtName.description: The name of a Route Map.

fastpathRoutePolicyStmtSeqNum.name: fastpathRoutePolicyStmtSeqNum
fastpathRoutePolicyStmtSeqNum.description: Route Maps are linked together using sequence numbers. All Route Maps with the same index and with different sequence numbers are linked together and processed in order of increasing sequence number.

fastpathRoutePolicyStmtAction.name: fastpathRoutePolicyStmtAction
fastpathRoutePolicyStmtAction.description: The action associated with this route-map statement. This can be either Permit/Deny

fastpathRoutePolicyStmtMatchIpv4AclList.name: fastpathRoutePolicyStmtMatchIpv4AclList
fastpathRoutePolicyStmtMatchIpv4AclList.description: The string containing a list of IPv4 ACLs. This list contains either IPV4 standard ACL/IPV4 extended ACL/ named IPv4 ACL. In a single match statement, up to a maximum of 16 IPV4 ACLs can be included.

fastpathRoutePolicyStmtMatchIpv4AclDelLi.name: fastpathRoutePolicyStmtMatchIpv4AclDelList
fastpathRoutePolicyStmtMatchIpv4AclDelLi.description: The string containing a list of IPv4 ACLs. This list contains either IPV4 standard ACL/IPV4 extended ACL/ named IPv4 ACL. In a single match statement, up to a maximum of 16 IPV4 ACLs can be included.This list is used to delete already configured match list of IPv4 ACLs in route-map statement.Earlier this list should have configured through MIB object fastpathRoutePolicyStmtMatchIpv4AclList

fastpathRoutePolicyStmtMatchMacAclList.name: fastpathRoutePolicyStmtMatchMacAclList
fastpathRoutePolicyStmtMatchMacAclList.description: The string containing a list of MAC ACLs. This list contains upto 16 MAC ACL names that can be included in a match statement.

fastpathRoutePolicyStmtMatchMacAclDelLis.name: fastpathRoutePolicyStmtMatchMacAclDelList
fastpathRoutePolicyStmtMatchMacAclDelLis.description: The string containing a list of MAC ACLs. This list contains upto 16 MAC ACL names that can be included in a match statement. This MIB object is used to delete MAC ACL lists matched in a route-map statement via fastpathRoutePolicyStmtMatchMacAclList.

fastpathRoutePolicyStmtMatchPacketLength.name: fastpathRoutePolicyStmtMatchPacketLengthRangeMin
fastpathRoutePolicyStmtMatchPacketLength.description: Minimum value in the packet length range in a match length term. A value of zero is used to disable/remove minimum length configuration.

fastpathRoutePolicyStmtMatchPacketLength.name: fastpathRoutePolicyStmtMatchPacketLengthRangeMax
fastpathRoutePolicyStmtMatchPacketLength.description: Maximum value in the packet length range in a match length term. A value of zero is used to disable/remove maximum length configuration.

fastpathRoutePolicyStmtSetIpNextHopList.name: fastpathRoutePolicyStmtSetIpNextHopList
fastpathRoutePolicyStmtSetIpNextHopList.description: The string containing a list of next-hop IP addresses. Upto a maximum of 16 IP addresses can be specified

fastpathRoutePolicyStmtSetIpNextHopDelLi.name: fastpathRoutePolicyStmtSetIpNextHopDelList
fastpathRoutePolicyStmtSetIpNextHopDelLi.description: The string containing a list of next-hop IP addresses. Upto a maximum of 16 IP addresses can be specified.This MIB object is used to delete IP next-hop list configured via fastpathRoutePolicyStmtSetIpNextHopList

fastpathRoutePolicyStmtSetDefaultIpNextH.name: fastpathRoutePolicyStmtSetDefaultIpNextHopList
fastpathRoutePolicyStmtSetDefaultIpNextH.description: The string containing a list of default next-hop IP addresses. Upto a maximum of 16 IP addresses can be specified

fastpathRoutePolicyStmtSetDefaultIpNextH.name: fastpathRoutePolicyStmtSetDefaultIpNextHopDelList
fastpathRoutePolicyStmtSetDefaultIpNextH.description: The string containing a list of default next-hop IP addresses. Upto a maximum of 16 IP addresses can be specified.This MIB object is used to delete IP default next-hop list configured via fastpathRoutePolicyStmtSetDefaultIpNextHopList

fastpathRoutePolicyStmtSetIpPrecedence.name: fastpathRoutePolicyStmtSetIpPrecedence
fastpathRoutePolicyStmtSetIpPrecedence.description: IP Precedence value to be remarked. This is specified through set clause in route-map statement. In order to remove configured precedence value, use invalid(8) option.

fastpathRoutePolicyStmtSetIntfNull0.name: fastpathRoutePolicyStmtSetIntfNull0
fastpathRoutePolicyStmtSetIntfNull0.description: Specifying null0 as an interface in a route-map statement

fastpathRoutePolicyIfTable.name: fastpathRoutePolicyIfTable
fastpathRoutePolicyIfTable.description: A table of interfaces on which route-map is applied.

fastpathRoutePolicyIfIndex.name: fastpathRoutePolicyIfIndex
fastpathRoutePolicyIfIndex.description: Interface to which route-map needs to be applied or Interface from which route-map needs to be removed.

fastpathRoutePolicyIfName.name: fastpathRoutePolicyIfName
fastpathRoutePolicyIfName.description: The name of a Route Map.

fastpathRoutePolicyIfRowStatus.name: fastpathRoutePolicyIfRowStatus
fastpathRoutePolicyIfRowStatus.description: Controls creation and deletion of Row Status entries.
